<exercise checkit-seed="0009" checkit-slug="G2" checkit-title="Volume">
    <statement>
        <p> A pyramid is positioned flat side down and a rectangular prism is attached cleanly to the bottom of the pyramid. The dimensions of the shape are as follows: The pyramid has base length 7, base width 7, and altitude 6, and the rectangular prism has height 10, where everything is measured in meters.
            <ol>
                <li>Sketch a drawing of this situation to the best of your ability.</li>
                <li>Find the total volume of this shape.</li>
            </ol>
        </p>
    </statement>
    <answer>
        <p>
            The volume is <m>V \approx 588.0</m> <m>m^3</m>. This was computed using the formula <m>V = \frac{1}{3}l\ell w h_1 + \ell w h_2</m>.
        </p>
    </answer>
</exercise>
